The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Fog bogs down air schedules

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Fog is throwing flight schedules haywire at the airport.

 On Wednesday night, two private airlines? flights to Calcutta from Mumbai and Bangkok were diverted due to fog at the city airport.

 On Thursday morning, a few flights to Delhi were delayed due to fog there. Among the delayed flights was Indian Airlines? 7 am service to the Capital. It left at 7.30 am.

 The Air Sahara flight from Mumbai was diverted to Lucknow, while a Thai Airways flight from Bangkok to Calcutta returned to Bangkok.

 Both flights landed in Calcutta on Thursday afternoon, said airport officials. 

 The passengers of the Air Sahara flight alleged that the arrangements at Lucknow were not satisfactory.

 A.K. Das, director-in-charge of meteorological office at the airport, said the fog would continue to hamper flight schedules till mid-February. ?Visibility starts decreasing from 5 pm and gets as low as 500 m,? he said.




